-- Olympus Panel Urges Suing Executives, Kyodo Says
-- B y   C h r i s   C o o p e r
-- 2012-01-08T04:40:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-08/olympus-panel-urges-suing-executives-kyodo-says-correct-.html
     (Corrects attribution in headline, story.)  Olympus Corp. (7733)  should seek damages of
more than 90 billion yen ($1.2 billion) from more than 10
current and past executives, including President Shuichi
Takayama, for covering up massive losses, according to an
independent panel, the Kyodo news service reported. Takayama is
preparing to resign and will hold a press conference tomorrow,
the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Chris Cooper  in Tokyo at 
